de.unihannover.se.iviewxjava.iviewx.data

Class ETEvent

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.unihannover.se.iviewxjava.iviewx.data.ETEvent
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ChronologicComparable<ETEvent>

    public class ETEvent
extends Object
implements ChronologicComparable<ETEvent>
    Stores eyetracking event information.

    Eyetracking events are fixation events.
    Fixation means a fixation of a screen coordinate for a given time period.

      • chrCompareTo

        public int chrCompareTo(ETEvent other)
        Compares this event with the other for chronological order. Returns a negative integer, zero, or a positive integer as this events start timestamp is less than, equal to, or greater than the other events start timestamp.

        Note: This imposes a chronological order based on when the events started, not when they ended or how long they lasted.

        Specified by:
        chrCompareTo in interface ChronologicComparable<ETEvent>
        Parameters:
        other - The Object to be compared
        Returns:
        A negative integer, zero, or a positive integer as this events start timestamp is less than, equal to, or greater than the other events start timestamp
